### 4. Teacher Module
Cleaned up the [TeacherService](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/nestjs/edu-vacation/src/modules/teacher/teacher.service.ts#6-40) signature.
*   **Updated [TeacherService](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/nestjs/edu-vacation/src/modules/teacher/teacher.service.ts#6-40)**: Removed `Types.ObjectId` from parameter types. Utilizing `CourseRepository.findByTeacher`.
*   **Updated [TeacherController](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/nestjs/edu-vacation/src/modules/teacher/teacher.controller.ts#15-47)**: Boundary conversion using `user._id.toString()`.

## The New Architectural Boundary
Mongoose is now contained strictly behind the Repository wall. 

```mermaid
graph TD
    Controller["Controller Layer\n(Extracts User, Converts _id to string)"] --> Service["Service Layer\n(Pure Business Logic, Plain Strings)"]
    Service --> Repository["Repository Layer\n(Converts strings to Types.ObjectId, runs $push/aggregate)"]
    Repository --> DB[(MongoDB / Mongoose)]
```

## Verification
*   We ran `npm run build`.
*   **Result**: 0 TypeScript compilation errors. The types correctly align across the fully decoupled boundaries.
